            <h4 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h4>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Login:</strong> Use your assigned credentials. Contact your administrator if you don’t have access.</li>
                <li><strong>Navigation:</strong> Use the main menu to access Backups, Restores, Snapshots, Jobs, Settings, and SnapMirror relationships.</li>
                <li><strong>Dashboard Overview:</strong> Review system status, storage health, and recent activity after login.</li>
            </ol>

            <hr />

            <h4 id="main-features">Main Features</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Backup Scheduling:</strong> Schedule recurring backups for selected VMs or entire storage. Supports daily, weekly, or hourly cycles and application-aware backups.</li>
                <li><strong>Manual Backups:</strong> Run instant backups of VMs or volumes, with options for crash-consistent or application-aware (IO Freeze, Proxmox Snapshot, Include RAM) operations.</li>
                <li><strong>Snapshot Management:</strong> View and manage snapshots for NetApp volumes, mount snapshots for inspection or recovery, and lock critical snapshots.</li>
                <li><strong>Restore:</strong> Restore VMs from available backups/snapshots, with options to rename, disconnect from the network, or use FlexClone for testing.</li>
                <li><strong>Storage & Cluster Integration:</strong> Automatically detects connected Proxmox clusters and NetApp controllers, groups shared storage, and tracks all associated VMs.</li>
                <li><strong>SnapMirror:</strong> Visualize and manage SnapMirror relationships for replication between primary and secondary NetApp controllers.</li>
                <li><strong>Job & Task Monitoring:</strong> Track all ongoing, completed, failed, or cancelled jobs in real time. Cancel or retry operations as needed.</li>
            </ul>

            <hr />

            <h4 id="common-tasks">Common Tasks</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>1. Creating a Backup Schedule:</strong>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Go to <b>Backup</b> &rarr; <b>Schedules</b>.</li>
                        <li>Click <b>Add Schedule</b>.</li>
                        <li>Fill in the schedule details: name, backup type, frequency, VMs/storage, retention policy, and options like application-aware backup.</li>
                        <li>Click <b>Save</b>. The schedule will appear in the list and run at the defined times.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>2. Running a Manual Backup:</strong>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Go to <b>Proxmox Storage</b>.</li>
                        <li>Select the storage, click <b>Backup Now</b>.</li>
                        <li>Choose backup options, then confirm to start.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>3. Restoring a VM:</strong>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Go to <b>Restore</b>.</li>
                        <li>Select the desired backup record or snapshot.</li>
                        <li>Follow the restore wizard to choose the target name, storage, and network settings.</li>
                        <li>Click <b>Restore</b> to start the process. You can monitor the restore job status on the <b>Jobs</b> page.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>4. Managing Snapshots:</strong>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Go to <b>Snapshots</b>.</li>
                        <li>Expand volumes to see available snapshots.</li>
                        <li>Mount snapshots as needed.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>5. Monitoring Jobs:</strong>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Go to <b>Jobs</b>.</li>
                        <li>See all running, completed, failed, or cancelled operations.</li>
                        <li>Cancel jobs directly from this page.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ul>

