            <h4 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h4>
            <div>
                <strong>Q: How do I know if my backup succeeded?</strong>
                <p>A: Go to the <b>Jobs</b> page. Completed jobs will show status “Completed”. Failed jobs will be marked with an error message and details.</p>

                <strong>Q: What is an application-aware backup?</strong>
                <p>A: It ensures applications (like databases) are in a consistent state by temporarily pausing I/O (IO Freeze) or using Proxmox snapshot features during backup.</p>

                <strong>Q: Can I restore to a new VM name or without network connection?</strong>
                <p>A: Yes. The restore wizard allows you to rename the VM and optionally restore it with the network interface disconnected.</p>

                <strong>Q: How do I change the backup retention policy?</strong>
                <p>A: Edit the backup schedule and adjust the “Retention” settings (number of backups and unit: days, weeks, etc.).</p>

                <strong>Q: I see a “Warning” on a storage. What does it mean?</strong>
                <p>A: Warnings are shown if a storage is unreachable or there are issues with the connection. Check network and NetApp system status.</p>

                <strong>Q: How do I add or configure a Proxmox cluster or NetApp controller?</strong>
                <p>A: Go to <b>Settings</b>, use the <b>Proxmox</b> or <b>NetApp</b> tabs to define or edit cluster/controller settings. Save credentials and test the connection.</p>

                <strong>Q: Can I view or manage SnapMirror replication?</strong>
                <p>A: Yes. Use the <b>SnapMirror</b> menu to see all relationships, replication lag, health, and status.</p>
            </div>

